Installing Python 3.6 from testing in Ubuntu
20180609

NOTE: Packages under the test repo are experimental and are not recommended for installation as it is hard to undo

Open sources.list file
1. sudo [file editor] /etc/apt/sources.list
* File editor can be nano, vi, notepadqq, etc.

2. Add this line in sources.list
# Ubuntu test repository (inclues Python 3.6 package)
deb http://ftp.de.debian.org/debian testing main

3. Check if 00local file exists
cd /etc/apt/apt.conf.d
ll -s

4. If 00local doesn't exist, create the file
sudo touch 00local

5. Add 'APT::Default-Release "stable";' via tee
echo 'APT::Default-Release "stable";' | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/00local

6. Update PPA repository list
sudo apt-get update

7. Install Python 3.6 from test
sudo apt-get -t testing install python3.6

